column7: Tailored to follow the organ system courses in allowing medical students to learn the structure and function of the circulatory, respiratory, renal, digestive, neuro-musculoskeletal, genitourinary and reproductive systems, as well as to ways to integrate ethical issues into the study and application of anatomy. No graduate credit. 0 professional hours. Approved for S/U grading only. May be repeated in separate semesters. Prerequisite: Restricted to students enrolled in the Carle Illinois College of Medicine curriculum.
